{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Plan review round 2 disposition (all five advisories accepted and remediated): (1) aligned the legacy inference acceptance-test selector with the planned pytest name; (2) defined the exact shared LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID constants, their values, location, producer use, and reducer use; (3) specified the SNAPSHOT strip guard as a contract test over _snapshot_strip_keys() with an explicit disjointness assertion; (4) clarified rollback/recompaction behavior: generic compiled-state restore plus the established strip policy preserves unknown provenance keys across immediate pre-feature recompaction, so rollback retains reader/schema support where possible; and (5) assigned SNAPSHOT output parity documentation and its schema-coverage/lint proof to child 568c. File-impact and verification metadata now match those edits."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784261206573426001,"uuid":"71f40b7a-c353-46c7-8907-159181ecda46"}